timing_socv_v...ultiplier_mode(25.10)    timing_socv_v...ultiplier_mode(25.10)

Name
       timing_socv_view_based_nsigma_multiplier_mode

Syntax
       timing_socv_view_based_nsigma_multiplier_mode {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables  setting  of view-based separate setup and hold sigma multipli-
       ers.

       By default or with an explicit true setting, the timing system is  con-
       figured  to  support  different N-sigma multiplier values for Setup vs.
       Hold - and for different analysis views. The specific N-sigma multipli-
       ers can be set using the set_socv_reporting_nsigma_multiplier command.

       In earlier releases, the timing_set_nsigma_multiplier  global  variable
       was used to specify a single N-sigma value that was used for both Setup
       and  Hold  analysis  across all analysis views. To continue using older
       scripts    with    this    control,    you    can    set    the    tim-
       ing_socv_view_based_nsigma_multiplier_mode global variable to false.

       Note:  This  backward compatibility option will not be supported in fu-
       ture releases. It is recommended to migrate your scripts to use the new
       view-based methodology.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

